  "text": "Fiber size variability and type-1 fiber predominance are the usual features with variable findings, such as muscle fiber necrosis and regeneration, and endomysial connective tissue proliferation [CITATION_1] . In one form of SEPN1-related myopathy, a congenital myopathy, multiminicore disease, with nondystrophic pathology is seen (multiple corelike areas of sarcoplasmic disorganization associated with mitochondrial depletion) [CITATION_2] .",
